Nigeria’s Lagos State Plans 114 MW Power Plant, ThisDay Reports

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-26T07:50:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/nigeria-s-lagos-state-plans-114-mw-power-plant-thisday-reports.html
Nigeria ’s Lagos state, which includes
the country’s commercial capital, plans to build a 114 megawatt
power plant to supply its major business districts,  ThisDay 
reported, citing the state governor, Babatunde Fashola.  The plant will be financed by private industry and is
expected to be completed 24 months after inception, the Lagos-
based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 